HTML Boilerplate is basically called below basic strucure of the html
write "!" and press enter you will get entire below html Boilerplate

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    
</body>
</html>
--------------------------------
inline css
<h1 style="background-color: blue;"> fayaz</h1>
<h1 attribute="value">fgdg</h1>
<h1 attribute="properties:value">sdfsdgsd</h1>

internal css
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <style>
        h1{color:green;font-size:10px;}
        </style>
    <title>Document</title>
</head>
<body>
    
</body>
</html>
----------------------------------
===element selector===
h1{ color: blue }
(h1) means element selector

===class selector ===
.heading{ color: red}
"." means class

<h1 class="heading">gfhfhfh</h1>

===id selector ====
#main {color:red}
"#" means Id
<h1 id="main">fgdfgdgrd</h1>

id is used for one element in the page like h1, header,footer tag, 
while class is usedfor many elements like paragraph, button etc


===attribute selector===
p[draggable] { color: red;}

draggable is the attribute
<p>sfdfs</p>
<p draggable="true">sdsdgsd</p> it select this

p[draggable="true"] { color: red;}
<p draggable="true"> fhdd </p>

===universal selector===
*{color:red;}

px
pt
em (if parent tag font-size 20px then 1em=20px,2em=40px)
rem (if root tag like html font-size is 20px then 1rem =20px)
vh viewport height (size of screen) like height :100vh

www.googlefonts.com

use googlefonts link in html head tag
<head>
    <link href="https://googlefonts......." />
</head>

<h1 style="font-family: paste role;"></h1>

